headline: Assessing Raymond James After Its Big Run and Wealth Management Expansion in 2025
summary: If you are wondering whether Raymond James Financial is still worth buying after its big run, or if most of the upside is already priced in, this article will walk through what the numbers say about value. At a recent price of around $163.85, the stock has dipped about 1.2% over the last month but is still up 5.7% year to date and 181.2% over five years, which points to both staying power and shifting expectations.
